{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Checkbox is a UI element that allows to select multiple options from a set of mutually non exclusive choices."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Checkbox item covers a wider range of contexts by allowing to toggle the visibility of additional text labels and icon assets.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate\/init(_:selection:description:icon:flipIcon:isReversed:isError:errorText:isReadOnly:hasDivider:constrainedMaxWidth:action:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate\/body"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate\/View-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudscheckboxitemindeterminate"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"]},{"content":[{"anchor":"Layouts","level":2,"text":"Layouts","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the component has a leading indicator, a label and optional helper texts, and an optional trailing decorative icon"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"inverse"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": like the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" layout but with a trailing checkbox indicator and a leading optional image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Indicator-states","level":2,"text":"Indicator states","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The checkbox indicator has three available states:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"selected"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": the checkbox is filled with a tick, the user has made the action to select the checkbox"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"unselected"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": the checkbox is empty, does not contain a tick, the user has made the action to unselect or did not select yet the checkbox"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"indeterminate"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": mike a prefilled or preticked checkbox, the user did not do anything on it yet"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need a checkbox with only two states to manage use instead ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Particular-cases","level":2,"text":"Particular cases","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" can be related to an error situation, for example troubles for a formular.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A dedicated look and feel is implemented for that if the ","type":"text"},{"code":"isError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag is risen.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In that case if the component displayed an icon, this icon will be replaced automatically by an error icon.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In addition, the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" can be in read only mode, i.e. the user cannot interact with the component yet","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"but this component must not be considered as disabled.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The component does not follow the right-to-left (RTL) \/ left-to-right (LTR) mode returned by the system as it could have some meaning","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to have for example the indicator in trailing position for LTR mode and vice versa.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However, if the component has an icon in leading position (RTL mode) or in trailing position (LTR), the content of the icon is never changed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It could lead to a loss of meaning or semantics in the icon. Thus a specific flag can be used to flip the icon content whatever the layout direction is.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It prevents the user do implement its own rules to flip or not image.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","level":2,"text":"Accessibility considerations","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Voice Over"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" will use several elements to describe the component: if component disabled \/ read only, if error context, the label and helper texts and a custom checkbox trait.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Forbidden-by-design","level":2,"text":"Forbidden by design","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a read only component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both a read only and a disabled component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading"},{"code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have an indeterminate state checkbox","    @Published var selection: OUDSCheckboxIndicatorState = .indeterminate","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Hello world\", selection: $selection)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but in read only mode (user cannot interact yet, but not disabled).","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Hello world\", selection: $selection, isReadOnly: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label and a description as helper text.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Bazinga!\", selection: $selection, description: \"Doll-Dagga Buzz-Buzz Ziggety-Zag\")","","    \/\/ A trailing checkbox with a label, an helper text and an icon.","    \/\/ The reversed layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"We live in a fabled world\",","                                  selection: $selection,","                                  description: \"Of dreaming boys and wide-eyed girls\",","                                  isReversed: true,","                                  icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"))","","    \/\/ If on error, add an error message can help user to understand error context","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"We live in a fabled world\",","                                  selection: $selection,","                                  isError: true,","                                  errorText: \"Something wrong\",","                                  hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but disabled.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Hello world\", selection: $selection)","        .disabled(true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label and and icon but with the icon flipped vertically","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Cocorico !\",","                                  selection: $selection,","                                  icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","                                  flipIcon: true)","","    \/\/ Never disable a read only or an error-related checkbox as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Hello world\", selection: $selection, isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Hello world\", selection: $selection, isReadOnly: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want to manage the RTL mode quite easily and switch your layouts (flip image, indicator in RTL leading i.e. in the right):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Cocorico !\",","                                  selection: $selection,","                                  icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","                                  flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft,","                                  isReversed: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"text":"Suggestions","anchor":"Suggestions","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"According to the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-checkbox","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the checkbox by default must be used in unselected state."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-checkbox","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"unified-design-system.orange.com","type":"text"}],"overridingTitle":"unified-design-system.orange.com"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Themes rendering","anchor":"Themes-rendering","type":"heading"},{"level":3,"text":"Orange","anchor":"Orange","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Orange","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Orange Compact","anchor":"Orange-Compact","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_OrangeCompact","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Sosh","anchor":"Sosh","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Sosh","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Wireframe","anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Wireframe","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Version","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"2.4.0 (Figma component design version)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"},{"name":"Since","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"0.12.0","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate"},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Structure","title":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents29OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminateV","symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"platforms":[{"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"15.0","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"macOS"},{"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"16.0","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"1.0","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"visionOS"},{"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"11.0","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","kind":"identifier"}]},"references":{"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/Controls":{"title":"Controls","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png"}],"type":"topic","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls","url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/controls","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Some comp